PART 4: MATROID THEORY — CYCLE MATROID OF K_n
======================================================================
Spanning trees of K_n (bases of cycle matroid):
  K_2: 1 spanning trees
  K_3: 3 spanning trees
  K_4: 16 spanning trees
  K_5: 125 spanning trees
  K_6: 1296 spanning trees
  K_7: 16807 spanning trees
  K_8: 262144 spanning trees

Tutte polynomial evaluations for K_n:
  T_K_n(1,1) = n^(n-2) = spanning trees
  T_K_n(2,0) = n! = acyclic orientations of K_n
  T_K_n(0,2) = totally cyclic orientations

Acyclic orientations of K_n = n! = transitive tournaments = T(2,0):
  n=2: 2
  n=3: 6
  n=4: 24
  n=5: 120
  n=6: 720

